<section id="Copying_a_report" remap="TID_15784">
	<title>Copying a Report</title>
	<para>
		Use this feature to copy a report that is similar to one that you want to create. Then, you only need to make minor edits instead of creating an entirely new report.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Cloud Intelligence</guimenu><guisubmenu>Reports</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the <guimenu>Reports</guimenu> accordion and select the report that you want to copy.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Configuration</guilabel>), then click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1859.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Copy this report</guilabel>).
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				On the Columns tab, edit the <guilabel>Basic Report Info</guilabel> area to include a new <guilabel>Menu Name</guilabel>. Each <guilabel>Menu Name</guilabel> must be unique.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Make any other changes you need. See <xref linkend="Adding_a_Report" /> for details on the changes you can make.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>